ationalgoals1 = 1\n| nationalgoals2 = 0\n| nationalgoals3 = 0\n| nationalgoals4 = 1\n| nationalgoals5 = 0\n| manageryears1 = 2012\n| managerclubs1 = [[A.S.D. Citt\u00e0 di Marino|Marino]]\n}}\n'''Gennaro Scarlato''' (born 3 May 1977 in [[Naples]]) is an Italian [[association football]] manager and former player who played as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]].\n\n==Playing career==\n\n===International===\nHe was in the provisional squad of [[Italy national under-21 football team|Italian U-21 team]] in [[2000 UEFA European Under-21 Football Championship|2000 UEFA U-21 Championship]] and [[Football at the 2000 Summer Olympics|2000 Olympics]], but never made any appearance.\n\n==Coaching career==\nOn 19 September 2012, he became the new coach of [[A.S.D. Citt\u00e0 di Marino|Marino]] (head coach) in the [[Serie D]], in place of Nunzio Iardino who had resigned.<ref>http://www.marino24ore.it/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=2158:citta-di-marino-mister-iardino-si-e-dimesso&catid=49:calcio&Itemid=155</ref><ref>http://www.marino24ore.it/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=2176:citta-di-marino-il-presidente-ritira-le-dimissioni-scarlato-nuovo-mister&catid=49:calcio&Itemid=155</ref> On 30 October 2012, he was sacked.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.figc.it/nazionali/DettaglioConvocato?codiceConvocato=1510 FIGC] {{in lang|it}}\n*[http://www.acspezia.com/teamDetail.php?id=15 acspezia.com] {{in lang|it}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Scarlato, Gennaro}}\n[[Category:1977 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Naples]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:Italian footballers]]\n[[Category:Italy under-21 international footballers]]\n[[Category:Italy youth international footballers]]\n[[Category:S.S.C. Napoli players]]\n[[Category:L.R. Vicenza Virtus players]]\n[[Category:Torino F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Udinese Calcio players]]\n[[Ca